
[1]vigilance

   VIG'ILANCE, n. [L. vigilans. See Vigil.]

   1. Forbearance of sleep; a state of being awake.

   2. Watchfulness; circumspection; attention of the mind in discovering
   and guarding against danger, or providing for safety. Vigilance is a
   virtue of prime importance in a general. The vigilance of the dog is no
   less remarkable than his fidelity.

   3. Guard; watch.

   In at this gate none pass the vigilance here plac'd.
